sentences: Marco Antonio Solís Sosa (born 29 December 1959) is a Mexican musician, singer, composer, and record producer.
In 1975  he co-founded Los Bukis, of which he was the lead vocalist and guitarist.
Solís released his first solo album, En Pleno Vuelo in 1996 by Fonovisa Records.
In 1995, after almost 20 years of working with the group, he decided to pursue a solo career.
On 5 August 2010, Solís received his star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame.
His album, "Gracias Por Estar Aquí", was released 22 October 2013 and debuted at #1 on Billboard's Top Latin Albums chart.
Solís returned to Billboard’s Regional Mexican Airplay chart for the first time in over two decades as “Se Veía Venir” climbed to No. 1 on the ranking dated October 2, 2021.

Solís provided the Spanish-dubbing of Ernesto de la Cruz, the main antagonist of the 2017 Disney-Pixar film Coco.
The band split up after nearly two decades of success, with Solís pursuing a solo career.
In 1995, after almost 20 years of working with the group, he decided to pursue a solo career.
He went on tour to promote his album Gracias Por Estar Aqui a few weeks after.
Solís returned to Billboard’s Regional Mexican Airplay chart for the first time in over two decades as “Se Veía Venir” climbed to No. 1 on the ranking dated October 2, 2021.
